Maybe the problem is that you are calling the &quot;GRI30&quot; function.  You  
can&#39;t do this - it is hardwired to GRI 3.0.  But all you need to do  
is go to the data directory, get file gri30.cti, save it as something  
else (e.g. &quot;my_modified_mech.cti&quot;), and then edit this cti file as  
you like.

Then in your script import this model by something like this:

gas = importPhase(&#39;my_modified_mech.cti&#39;)



